"},{"conversion_notes":"The Python string utility becomes a typed Jac ability. The boolean negation is written with Jac/Python-style not, and the palindrome check uses index arithmetic rather than slicing to keep the conversion explicit.","jac_code":"def is_palindrome(text: str) -> bool {
    left = 0;
    right = len(text) - 1;
    while left < right {
        if text[left] != text[right] {
            return False;
        }
        left = left + 1;
        right = right - 1;
    }
    return True;
}
","python_code":"def is_palindrome(text):
    left = 0
